{{Infobox language |name=Laoseng |nativename= |states=[[Laos]] |region= |ethnicity= |speakers=? |date= |ref= |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=([[Tibeto-Burman languages|Tibeto-Burman]]) |fam3=[[Lolo–Burmese languages|Lolo–Burmese]] |fam4=[[Loloish languages|Loloish]] |fam5=[[Southern Loloish languages|Southern]] |fam6=[[Bisoid languages|Bisoid]] |iso3=none |glotto=none }}
'''Laoseng''' (''{{IPA|lao˨˩sɛŋ˨˩}}''; also known as ''{{IPA|kʰa˥}}'') is a [[Loloish language]] of northern [[Laos]]. David Bradley (2007)<ref name="Bradley2007">Bradley, David (2007). "Language Endangerment in China and Mainland Southeast Asia". In Matthias Brenzinger, ed. ''Language diversity endangered''. New York: Mouton de Gruyter.</ref> lists ''law˨˩sɛŋ˨˩'' as the autonym.
Kingsada (1999) documents ''{{IPA|lao˨˩sɛŋ˨˩}}'' of Chaho village, [[Boun Tay District|Bun Tay District]], [[Phongsaly Province]], while Kato (2008) documents ''{{IPA|kʰa˥}}'' of Namnat village, [[Yot Ou District|Nyot U District]], [[Phongsaly Province]].
